#. Tag: title
#: sled_planning.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "Planning for &sled;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:15
#, no-c-format
msgid "This chapter describes some basic considerations before installing &productname;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:26
#, no-c-format
msgid "This chapter is addressed mainly to corporate system administrators who face the task of having to deploy &sledreg; at their site. Rolling out &sled; to an entire site should involve careful planning and consideration of the following questions:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: sled_planning.xml:34
#, no-c-format
msgid "For which purpose will the &sled; workstations be used?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:36
#, no-c-format
msgid "Determine the purpose for which &sled; should be used and make sure that hardware and software with the ability to match these requirements are used. Consider testing your setup on a single machine before rolling it out to the entire site."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: sled_planning.xml:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "How many workstations should be installed?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "Determine the scope of your deployment of &sled;. Depending on the number of installations planned, consider different approaches to the installation or even a mass installation using &sle;s unique &ay; or &kiwi; technology."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: sled_planning.xml:56
#, no-c-format
msgid "How do you get software updates for your deployment?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "All patches provided by &suse; for your product are available for download to registered users at <link xlink:href=\"http://download.suse.com/\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: sled_planning.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do you need help for your local deployment?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:68
#, no-c-format
msgid "&suse; provides training, support, and consulting for all topics pertaining to &sled;. Find more information about this at <link xlink:href=\"http://www.suse.com/products/desktop/\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sled_planning.xml:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terminology"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the following sections, the system to hold your new &productname; installation is called <emphasis>target system</emphasis> or <emphasis>installation target</emphasis> . The term <emphasis>repository</emphasis> (previously called <quote>installation source</quote> ) is used for all sources of installation data. This includes physical media, such as CD and DVD, and network servers distributing the installation data in your network."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sled_planning.xml:89
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hardware Requirements"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "For a standard installation of &sled;, including the desktop environment and a wealth of applications, the following configuration is recommended:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:99
#, no-c-format
msgid "Intel Pentium IV, 2.4 GHz or higher or any AMD64 or &intel64; processor"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "1&ndash;2 physical CPUs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "512 MB physical RAM or higher"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "3 GB of available disk space or more"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:120
#, no-c-format
msgid "1024 x 768 display resolution (or higher)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sled_planning.xml:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reasons to Use &sled;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "Let the following items guide you in your selection of &sled; and determining the purpose of the installed systems:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: sled_planning.xml:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wealth of Applications"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:138
#, no-c-format
msgid "&sled;'s broad offer of software makes it appeal to both professional users in a corporate environment and to home users or users in smaller networks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: sled_planning.xml:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ease of Use"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:148
#, no-c-format
msgid "&sled; comes with the enterprise-ready desktop environment &gnome;. It enables users to comfortably adjust to a Linux system while maintaining their efficiency and productivity. <phrase os=\"sled\">To explore &gnome; in detail, refer to the <xref linkend=\"book.gnomeuser\"/>.</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: sled_planning.xml:158
#, no-c-format
msgid "Support for Mobile Users"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "With the NetworkManager technology fully integrated into &sled; and its two desktop environments, mobile users will enjoy the freedom of easily joining and switching wired and wireless networks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: sled_planning.xml:168
#, no-c-format
msgid "Seamless Integration into Existing Networks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:170
#, no-c-format
msgid "&sled; was designed to be a versatile network citizen. It cooperates with various different network types:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sled_planning.xml:175
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pure Linux Networks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:176
#, no-c-format
msgid "&sled; is a complete Linux client and supports all the protocols used in traditional Linux and Unix* environments. It integrates well with networks consisting of other &suselinux; or &sle; machines. LDAP, NIS, and local authentication are supported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: sled_planning.xml:184
#, no-c-format
msgid "Windows Networks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:185
#, no-c-format
msgid "&sled; supports Active Directory as an authentication source. It offers you all the advantages of a secure and stable Linux operating system plus convenient interaction with other Windows clients, as well as the means to manipulate your Windows user data from a Linux client. Explore this feature in detail in <xref linkend=\"cha.security.ad\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: sled_planning.xml:209
#, no-c-format
msgid "Application Security with &aa;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: sled_planning.xml:211
#, no-c-format
msgid "&sled; enables you to secure your applications by enforcing security profiles tailor-made for your applications. To learn more about &aa;, refer to <link xlink:href=\"http://www.suse.com/documentation/apparmor/\"/> ."
msgstr ""

